tool.name: CenterlineStations
tool.displayname: 3. Create GGL Table and Centerline Stations

param.name: InputCenterlineRouted
param.dialogReference:
First, we input the Routed Centerline Feature Class created in Step 2.

ATTENTION!!! Make sure you are selecting the ROUTED Centerline created in Step 2, and not the Centerline created in Step 1.
param.pythonReference: Creates a variable that references the Routed Centerline Feature Class

param.name: RouteID
param.dialogReference: Next, we use the dropdown to select the ROUTEID. This is a maintenance/validation step intended to reduce potential user error.

param.name: InputCrossSection
param.dialogReference: Now, we input the Cross Section Feature Class created in Step 2.

param.name: bufferBoolean
param.dialogReference:
Now, you have to decide whether or not to include a Centerline Buffer.

The default is "No" which builds the GGL using only the Centerline Station Elevations.

It is recommended that you first start with NO buffer.

If you select "Yes" you will need to input a Buffer distance (m). This will include additional elevations for each centerline station.

More data doesn't mean better results.

The buffer distance sets the perpendicular extent from the centerline that additional elevations are evaluated (1m steps).

param.name: buffer
param.dialogReference: Your centerline buffer aim to include only the fluvial valley floor.

param.name: InputLidar
param.datatype: Raster Layer or Layer or Mosaic Dataset or Mosaic Layer or Raster Dataset or Raster Data Layer
param.dialogReference: Finally, we input the LiDAR Digital Elevation Model.

tool.summary:
This third tool creates the centerline stations with elevation values and created the Geomorphic Grade Line table.

  1. First, we input the Routed Centerline Feature Class created in Step 2.

  2. Next, we use the dropdown to select the ROUTEID. This is a maintenance/validation step intended to reduce potential user error.

  3. Then, we input the Cross Section Feature Class created in Step 2.

  4. Now, you have to decide whether or not to include a Centerline Buffer

  5. Default value is 1, or the Centerline Station point elevation.

  6. Finally, we input the LiDAR Digital Elevation Model.
